    "In 2004, conference proceedings appeared as the popular document type, however as the field evolved articles took over and we can see an increase after the year 2019 compared to conference proceedings.",
    "This is understandable as the publication by document type might have been influenced by the COVID-19 lockdown across the globe, this fact has made TM researchers swap the document type preferences from conference proceedings to articles.",
    "Table 3 shows that Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers Inc (IEEE) (3026), Springer (2205), Elsevier (1332) and the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) (1213) are the publishers that produced the largest number of publications on TM across the years.",
    "Furthermore, as shown in Table 4, dominant sources chosen to disseminate research results on TM are conference proceedings belonging to the computer science subject area.",
    "Figure 3 presents the plot of the publications by subject area and their citation impact."
